Apparently the binary windows version of Cantera 1.5.4 has a broken 
version of the Chemkin-to-Cantera input file converter utility, 
ck2cti.exe.

A new version for Windows has been posted to the "files" section of the 
user's group.  I have added to it a debugging feature, which prints 
low-level debugging information to the log file.  Hopefully this 
version will work on all Chemkin input files.  As far as I know, the 
linux and Mac versions have no problems.

  If for any reason this version fails on *any* valid Chemkin input 
file, please rerun it with the option '-d' and e-mail me the log file 
along with the Chemkin input file, and if necessary the thermo database 
file, and I will try to fix the problem. But HOPEFULLY this will not be 
necessary, and now it will just work...
